      <pubtit>The Second Dicova Challenge: Dataset and Performance Analysis for Diagnosis of Covid-19 Using Acoustics</pubtit>
      <p><img src="http://localhost:4000/images/pubpic/Pairs3.png" class="img-responsive" width="33%" style="float: left" /></p>
      <p>We use our atomic-scale scanning tunneling noise setup on a disordered superconductor, and discover a state above TC that, much like an ordinary metal, has no (pseudo)gap, but carries charge via paired electrons.</p>
      <p><em>Neeraj Kumar Sharma, Srikanth Raj Chetupalli, Debarpan Bhattacharya, Debottam Dutta, Pravin Mote, Sriram Ganapathy</em></p>
      <p><strong><a href="https://ieeexplore.ieee.org/abstract/document/9747188">ICASSP 374, 608 (2021)</a></strong></p>
