      <p><img src="http://localhost:4000/images/pubpic/TBG_SL.png" class="img-responsive" width="33%" style="float: left" /></p>
      <p>Why is there so much variation in TBG devices? And are open devices more disordered than encapsulated ones? We introduce a new method to continuously map inhomogeneities of a moirÃ© lattice and apply it to open-device TBG to show that twist angle variation is small over areas of hundreds of nm.</p>
      <p><em>Ananya Muguli, Lancelot Pinto, Neeraj Sharma, Prashant Krishnan, Prasanta Kumar Ghosh, Rohit Kumar, Shrirama Bhat, Srikanth Raj Chetupalli, Sriram Ganapathy, Shreyas Ramoji, Viral Nanda</em></p>
